						<p>This "inferior Russian armies" trope is not so well supported in reality. For one thing, you know the Germans stole the Blitzkrieg idea from the very Russians in question ? For the other thing, the KV and T designs were the best tanks of the war, because bigger isn't strictly better, nor more expensive nor more complex. On it goes, it's a lengthy discussion.</p>
<p>Army power is not based on numbers, it's based on men. Yes smaller countries have necessarily smaller stores of men, but this does not help larger countries necessarily. Which is why ISIS is beating the shit out of the US in the field ; something the US couldn't achieve should, eg, China's 300 mn strong army decide to land one day.</p>
